          <title>Bulls blow 21 point lead in 141-133 loss to Atlanta</title>
          <description><![CDATA[ATLANTA (AP) — Jalen Johnson had a career-high 30 points and the Atlanta Hawks rallied from a late 21-point deficit by scoring 50 points in the fourth quarter in a 141-133 win over the Chicago Bulls on Thursday night.]]></description>
